&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for Targeted General Practice Training (TGPT) programme at ST3 level in England and Scotland starting from Wednesday 4th August 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The application window opens on Tursday 5th November 2020 at 10:00 UK time and closes on Tuesday 1st December 2020 at 16:00 UK time. You will not be able to submit your application after this time. Please ensure that you have completed all the relevant sections of the application forms as missing information will deem your application incomplete and it will not be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must apply via our online recruitment system, Oriel. Oriel can be accessed from the link provided. Registration is available to applicants from Monday 2nd November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The qualifications and professional registration requirements plus other eligibility criteria can be found in the person specification. The person specification for this specialty is available from the Specialty Training website which can be accessed from Oriel. Please visit the GP National Recruitment Office (contact details can be accessed from Oriel) to find out the following information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Indicative number of vacancies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Likely locations of posts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expected rotation details&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Anticipated outcome of the training programme, subject to satisfactory progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel and relocation expenses policy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
